[
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"461444\">Sam Mohr</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/231634-beginners/topic/number.20ranges.20without.20heap.20allocations/near/465532329\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We have</p>\n<ul>\n<li>List.walk</li>\n<li>List.walkWithIndex</li>\n<li>List.walkWithIndexUntil</li>\n<li>List.walkUntil</li>\n<li>List.walkBackwards</li>\n<li>and so on...</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 465543139,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1724787130
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>here's an idea for how to simplify these: what if we collapsed all of these functions into two?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">walk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">state</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">walkWith</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">init</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">direction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">Forward</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Backward</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">U64</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">([</span><span class=\"kt\">Continue</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Stop</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">state</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>so <code>walkWith</code> always gives you the index (you can <code>_</code> it if you don't care), always lets you end early, and then lets you specify <code>Forward</code> (the default) or <code>Backward</code> (optionally) if you want that</p>",
        "id": 465543173,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1724787141
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>could also just put all the different options in one place:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">walkWith</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">[</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kt\">Index</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">U64</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kt\">IndexBackwards</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">U64</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kt\">Until</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">([</span><span class=\"kt\">Continue</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Stop</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">)),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kt\">BackwardsUntil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">([</span><span class=\"kt\">Continue</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Stop</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">)),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kt\">IndexUntil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">U64</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">([</span><span class=\"kt\">Continue</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Stop</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">)),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kt\">IndexBackwardsUntil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">U64</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">([</span><span class=\"kt\">C</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">S</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">)),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">state</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 465544697,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1724787640
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>kinda similar to what <code>List.range</code> does</p>",
        "id": 465545379,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1724787813
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We can't use <code>?</code> in the API today.</p>",
        "id": 465545795,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1724787911
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Though maybe we should just fix that</p>",
        "id": 465545879,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1724787932
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I looked once or twice before and wasnt really sure though</p>",
        "id": 465545951,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1724787948
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>As much as this is a little bit of runtime cost, I think either API would be a maintenance improvement on our end, and a discoverability improvement on the user's end</p>",
        "id": 465552592,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1724789284
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And generally inlining should fix the runtime cost</p>",
        "id": 465572405,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1724794693
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I do something like this for my 2d array library <a href=\"https://github.com/mulias/roc-array2d/blob/main/package/Array2D.roc#L440\">https://github.com/mulias/roc-array2d/blob/main/package/Array2D.roc#L440</a></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">WalkOptions</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">direction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">Forwards</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Backwards</span><span class=\"p\">],</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">orientation</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">Rows</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Cols</span><span class=\"p\">],</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">start</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Index2D</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span>\n\n<span class=\"nv\">walk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Array2D</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">WalkOptions</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">*</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Index2D</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">state</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">walk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">array</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">startState</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">options</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">direction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">options</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">direction</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">orientation</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Rows</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">start</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">walkStart</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">array</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">options</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">direction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">options</span>\n\n<span class=\"nv\">walkUntil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Array2D</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">WalkOptions</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">*</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Index2D</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">Continue</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Break</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"p\">])</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">state</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Using <code>WalkOptions *</code> in the type sig avoids the <code>?</code> bug. The <code>direction</code> field is required because it's used to set the default of <code>start</code> to the first/last index, and all the ways I tried to first get the optional <code>direction</code> and then use if for a different optional field were broken.</p>",
        "id": 465573192,
        "sender_full_name": "Elias Mulhall",
        "timestamp": 1724794879
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not saying you should do that - definitely better to fix optional record fields</p>",
        "id": 465573451,
        "sender_full_name": "Elias Mulhall",
        "timestamp": 1724794936
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>an argument in favor of 1 function apiece is that this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">walkBackwardsUntil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">initialState</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">elem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">...</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>...is nicer to write than:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">walkWith</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">initialState</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">BackwardsUntil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">elem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nf\">...</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 465574542,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1724795182
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>basically always requires parens</p>",
        "id": 465574594,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1724795195
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>where status quo does not</p>",
        "id": 465574628,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1724795203
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>Using <code>WalkOptions *</code> in the type sig avoids the <code>?</code> bug.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>That's a really cool fix. Make it have specialization to help roc generate correctly. Maybe we can somehow force all records with <code>?</code> to have a secret type variable and that will just fix our issues?</p>",
        "id": 465578329,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1724796761
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Like somehow we need roc to understand it needs to specialize the type</p>",
        "id": 465578371,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1724796779
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"281383\">Richard Feldman</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/simplifying.20walking.20API/near/465574542\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>an argument in favor of 1 function apiece is that this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">walkBackwardsUntil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">initialState</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">elem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">...</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>...is nicer to write than:</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">walkWith</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">initialState</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">BackwardsUntil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">elem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nf\">...</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Not only this, but the formatter is gonna put a bunch of newlines in there.</p>",
        "id": 465591017,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1724803896
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>the formatter is gonna put a bunch of newlines in there.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>That's something that's under our control :P</p>",
        "id": 465605503,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1724811041
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think <code>walkTry</code> is a useful member of the family, but it doesn't have backwards and indexed variants at the moment</p>",
        "id": 465683378,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Nuttall",
        "timestamp": 1724833148
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Trying to combine many things into <code>walkWith</code> makes it more complicated in my opinion. With separate functions, you can have a single example per function in the docs. With <code>walkWith</code> you'd have to provide a bunch, it seems like that would result in significant cognitive load. I already think <code>walk</code> is not easy to use.</p>",
        "id": 465692861,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1724835218
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>One half-way option is to always include the index. You can use <code>_</code> to ignore it if you don't need it. After using the function a heap of times it will just be normal to have it there, and less confusing.</p>",
        "id": 465693630,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1724835375
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is another case where iterators have an advantage cause you can decompose the pieces better.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">toIter</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">list</span>\n<span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Iter</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">reverse</span>\n<span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Iter</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">enumerate</span>\n<span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Iter</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">walk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">i</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 465804503,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1724860852
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You still need <code>walk</code>, <code>walkTry</code> and <code>walkUntil</code>, but it is a way simpler mental model</p>",
        "id": 465804631,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1724860891
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>kinda, but another way to look at it is that the current design offers a convenient one-function alternative to iterators <span aria-label=\"big smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"big smile\">:big_smile:</span> </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">toIter</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">list</span>\n<span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Iter</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">reverse</span>\n<span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Iter</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">enumerate</span>\n<span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Iter</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">walk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">i</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">walkBackwardsWithIndex</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">i</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 465806991,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1724861592
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's not true though</p>",
        "id": 465833301,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1724872170
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It only does so for lists</p>",
        "id": 465833310,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1724872174
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>As discussed elsewhere, there are other places where iterators would be nice.</p>",
        "id": 465833414,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1724872229
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(deleted)</p>",
        "id": 465833474,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1724872263
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"343810\">Brendan Hansknecht</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/simplifying.20walking.20API/near/465833414\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>As discussed elsewhere, there are other places where iterators would be nice.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I agree with this. Richard's example could be updated to any data structure just by updating the first line, like <code>Set.toIter</code></p>",
        "id": 465833630,
        "sender_full_name": "Kilian Vounckx",
        "timestamp": 1724872348
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, across our different data collections, an <code>Iter</code>/<code>Seq</code>/<code>Stream</code> type would be the single place to handle everything. If it compiles efficiently, requires fewer allocations, and is still expressive, I definitely prefer it to needing to learn different APIs for different types.</p>",
        "id": 465834356,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1724872670
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But I'm a big Rust fan, so I'm biased towards iterators for sure</p>",
        "id": 465834422,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1724872686
    }
]